50|$|In the United States, the Ku Klux Klan (KKK) is {{the group}} most {{associated}} with the <b>white</b> <b>supremacist</b> movement. Many <b>white</b> <b>supremacist</b> groups {{are based on the}} concept of preserving genetic purity, and they do not focus solely on discrimination based on skin color. The KKK's reasons for supporting racial segregation are not primarily based on religious ideals, but some Klan groups are openly Protestant. The KKK and other <b>white</b> <b>supremacist</b> groups like Aryan Nations, The Order and the White Patriot Party are considered antisemitic.|$|R
